x4freetext: Back-n facility of the China
Spallation Neutron Source (CSNS)
The neutron beam is produced through the
pulses of protons with an energy of 1.6 GeV and a
pulse frequency of 25 Hz, bombarding a tungsten
target. The Back-n white neutron beam line is
constructed 180 degree to the proton beam direction,
and the neutron flux can reach up to 1E7 n/cm2/s at
the experimental station.
The Back-n C6D6 detector system consists of
four C6D6 liquid scintillation detectors, one
aluminum detector`s brackets, and one aluminum sample
holder. The C6D6 detectors are placed upstream of the
neutron beam sample target to decrease the elastic
scattering neutron background, and the detector axis
is at an angle of 110 degree from the neutron beam.
The distance between the C6D6 detectors front center
to the sample target center was 150 mm and 80 mm from
the neutron beam axis.
SiMon detector for detection of triton and alpha
from 6Li(n,t+a) reaction.
The gold sample (Au) with a diameter of 50 mm, a
thickness of 1 mm, a weight of 37.93 g and an area of
19.63 cm2. The area density is 0.005907 atoms/barn.
The length of neutron flight path is
approximately 76 m.
Weighting function calculated by Geant4.
Absolute normalization to the 4.9 eV saturated
resonance.
for shape normalization
The factor fc was introduced for considering the
multi-elastic scattering of neutrons in the thick
sample, which is related to the absorption cross
section and the thickness of the sample. It is the
ratio of the mean neutron transmission length to the
target thickness.
Capture cross section derived from the capture yield
multiplied by the ENDF total cross section (sigma)
and divided by the absorption correction factor
1-exp(-n*t*sigma*fc), n is the density of the sample,
t is the thickness of the sample, fc is the fixed
factor of the sample thickness.
